    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "87427c91_28cdeb09",
        "filename": "go/gitstore/gitstore.go",
        "patchSetId": 51
      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-21T14:49:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This file seems to assume that we\u0027ll only have the BigTable implementation of GitStore.  Can we either remove this interface under that assumption or split up the interface from the implementation a bit?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 82,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 82,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "c4f191c33b4fff8e2380468771fa083f6d9c3ec8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b206ba24_7de3aa8e",
        "filename": "go/gitstore/gitstore.go",
        "patchSetId": 51
      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-21T22:26:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like having an interface for this, because that means we tightly control what functions we expose and we can mock it when necessary. For types concerned with I/O it makes sense IMO to have an interface even if we have never more than one implementation. \n\nIf we ever have another implementation of GitStore it could live alongside the BT base-one in here.",
      "parentUuid": "87427c91_28cdeb09",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 82,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 82,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "c4f191c33b4fff8e2380468771fa083f6d9c3ec8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f45cb3e1_01bc1699",
        "filename": "go/gitstore/gitstore.go",
        "patchSetId": 51
      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-22T17:56:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "SGTM.  As mentioned in person, I do think it might be useful to have a super-simple in-memory implementation for comparison\u0027s sake, and maybe an impl which is directly backed by a git.Repo, to bridge the transition over to BigTable.  For the record, when we expect to have multiple non-trivial implementations of a given interface (especially for DBs), I like this package structure:\n\ngo/my_interface: Contains the interface, shared constants and helper funcs, and black-box test code.\ngo/my_interface/impl1: Contains one implementation of the interface. Tests call into the test funcs in go/my_interface\ngo/my_interface/impl2: Another impl\n\nFor now, I think the current organization is fine.",
      "parentUuid": "b206ba24_7de3aa8e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 82,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 82,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "c4f191c33b4fff8e2380468771fa083f6d9c3ec8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
